20/06/2005
ISTANBUL, Turkey -- The outgoing US Ambassador to Turkey, Eric Edelman, said on Friday (17 June) that his country has always supported Turkey's modernisation and that the two countries are allies in the fight against terrorism.
Edelman resigned from the post in March.
Until a successor is appointed, US Embassy Counselor Nancy McEldowney will assume the ambassador's duties.
(TurkishPress.com - 19/06/05)
